Contents
[1, p. 69, lines 1-6] No kossi [=cosi?] presto no : [aria for S bc : the text is partly written in Kurrentschrift : 22 bars in A major] -- [2, p. 69, lines 5-8] Alle[gro] [for treble and bass in B minor : 10 bars] -- [3, p. 69, lines 9-11] [Recitative for S, b, lacking text except one syllable "Ah" on the third note : line 11 is a free hand stave added at the bottom of the page, first continuing the voice from line 9, and then the continuo from line 10, this then continues on a free hand stave to the right of line 8 : there is some loss of music from the bottom and right hand edges] -- [4, p. 70, lines 1-4] [Untexted fragment for SATB : 8 bars in B minor] -- [5, p. 70, lines 5-10] [Untitled movement for 2 trebles and bass in A minor : 27 bars, incomplete?]
[Collection of 5 musical sketches] : The Book of Kings. Ahab, Jezabel, Naboth, The Profet Elija / [by George Frideric Handel and/or others]
